Drug Interaction Prediction using Graph Attention Networks
A deep learning framework for predicting drug-drug interactions, drug-target associations, and drug-disease relationships using Graph Attention Networks (GAT) and multi-task learning on heterogeneous biomedical graphs.

Overview
This project implements a sophisticated drug interaction prediction system that leverages Graph Attention Networks to model complex relationships in biomedical data. The system integrates multiple data sources including molecular structures (SMILES), drug classifications (ATC codes), and interaction networks to predict potential drug interactions and discover new therapeutic applications.

Key Features
Graph Attention Networks (GAT): Multi-head attention mechanism for learning complex drug-drug, drug-target, and drug-disease relationships
Multi-Task Learning: Simultaneous prediction of multiple interaction types using shared representations
Heterogeneous Graph Integration: Combines drug similarity, molecular features, and interaction networks
Cold Start Handling: Specialized training strategies for new drugs with limited interaction data
Scaffold-Based Splitting: Rigorous evaluation using molecular scaffold-based train/test splits
Interpretability Analysis: Attention weight visualization and latent space exploration
Diversity Analysis: Comprehensive evaluation of prediction diversity and chemical space coverage
Ablation Studies: Systematic component analysis to understand model contributions
REST API: Production-ready Flask API for real-time predictions
Technology Stack
Deep Learning: PyTorch, PyTorch Geometric (GNN library)
Molecular Processing: RDKit (SMILES parsing, molecular fingerprints, scaffolds)
Graph Processing: NetworkX, DGL (Deep Graph Library)
Data Processing: NumPy, Pandas, scikit-learn
Visualization: Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly
API Framework: Flask, Flask-CORS
Data Sources: DrugBank XML, ATC classification system
